ction_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_e6y6WLAzzkn2CWz0WhQ7VtZg", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary libraries in R, specifically methylKit.\\n2. Read the bismark coverage files using methylKit::methRead with the specified parameters.\\n3. Unite the methylation data using methylKit::unite with the given parameters.\\n4. Save the united methylBase object as mk_united.rds.\\n5. Create a unite_stats.tsv file with the required statistics.\\n6. Check the output directory for the presence of unite_stats.tsv.\\n7. Submit the task as done if the file is present.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (469 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_e6y6WLAzzkn2CWz0WhQ7VtZg"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_1R6fy7Fh6r5vgmHr0cojVBeX", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile.list <- list(\\n  \\\"input/sampleA.bismark.cov\\\",\\n  \\\"input/sampleB.bismark.cov\\\",\\n  \\\"input/sampleC.bismark.cov\\\",\\n  \\\"input/sampleD.bismark.cov\\\"\\n)\\n\\n# Read the methylation data\\nmk_raw <- methRead(\\n  file.list,\\n  pipeline = \\\"bismarkCoverage\\\",\\n  assembly = \\\"mock_v1\\\",\\n  treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1),\\n  mincov = 4\\n)\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group = 1, destrand = FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, \\\"output/mk_united.rds\\\")\\n\\n# Create unite_stats.tsv\\nn_samples <- length(mk_united@sample.ids)\\nn_sites <- nrow(mk_united)\\nmin_per_group <- 1\\ndestrand <- FALSE\\nuse_db <- mk_united@dbtype\\nif (is.null(use_db)) use_db <- FALSE\\nelse use_db <- TRUE\\ndb_path <- mk_united@dbpath\\nif (is.null(db_path)) db_path <- \\\"NA\\\"\\n\\n# Write the statistics to a TSV file\\nwrite.table(\\n  data.frame(n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path),\\n  file = \\\"output/unite_stats.tsv\\\",\\n  sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\",\\n  row.names = FALSE,\\n  col.names = TRUE\\n)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (469 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_e6y6WLAzzkn2CWz0WhQ7VtZg"}], "next_observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var, xtabs\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    anyDuplicated, aperm, append, as.data.frame, basename, cbind,\n    colnames, dirname, do.call, duplicated, eval, evalq, Filter, Find,\n    get, grep, grepl, is.unsorted, lapply, Map, mapply, match, mget,\n    order, paste, pmax, pmax.int, pmin, pmin.int, Position, rank,\n    rbind, Reduce, rownames, sapply, saveRDS, table, tapply, unique,\n    unsplit, which.max, which.min\n\nLoading required package: S4Vectors\n\nAttaching package: \u2018S4Vectors\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:utils\u2019:\n\n    findMatches\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    expand.grid, I, unname\n\nLoading required package: IRanges\nLoading required package: GenomeInfoDb\nReceived list of locations.\nError in if (is.na(treatment)) stop(\"Treatment vector is missing.\") : \n  the condition has length > 1\nCalls: methRead -> methRead\nExecution halted\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_1R6fy7Fh6r