mark.cov`,\n`sampleD.bismark.cov` \u2014 tab-separated without headers, columns\n`(chrom, start, end, methylation_pct, count_methylated, count_unmethylated)`.\n\nLoad them with `methylKit::methRead(..., pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4)`,\nusing `treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1)` and assembly `mock_v1`. Then run\n`methylKit::unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)` and save:\n  - `output/mk_united.rds`: the united methylBase object (`saveRDS`).\n  - `output/unite_stats.tsv`: a single-row tab-separated table with columns\n    `n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path` (`write_tsv`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/unite_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: unite_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_e6y6WLAzzkn2CWz0WhQ7VtZg", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary libraries in R, specifically methylKit.\\n2. Read the bismark coverage files using methylKit::methRead with the specified parameters.\\n3. Unite the methylation data using methylKit::unite with the given parameters.\\n4. Save the united methylBase object as mk_united.rds.\\n5. Create a unite_stats.tsv file with the required statistics.\\n6. Check the output directory for the presence of unite_stats.tsv.\\n7. Submit the task as done if the file is present.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (469 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_e6y6WLAzzkn2CWz0WhQ7VtZg"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_1R6fy7Fh6r5vgmHr0cojVBeX", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfile.list <- list(\\n  \\\"input/sampleA.bismark.cov\\\",\\n  \\\"input/sampleB.bismark.cov\\\",\\n  \\\"input/sampleC.bismark.cov\\\",\\n  \\\"input/sampleD.bismark.cov\\\"\\n)\\n\\n# Read the methylation data\\nmk_raw <- methRead(\\n  file.list,\\n  pipeline = \\\"bismarkCoverage\\\",\\n  assembly = \\\"mock_v1\\\",\\n  treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1),\\n  mincov = 4\\n)\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group = 1, destrand = FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, \\\"output/mk_united.rds\\\")\\n\\n# Create unite_stats.tsv\\nn_samples <- length(mk_united@sample.ids)\\nn_sites <- nrow(mk_united)\\nmin_per_group <- 1\\ndestrand <- FALSE\\nuse_db <- mk_united@dbtype\\nif (is.null(use_db)) use_db <- FALSE\\nelse use_db <- TRUE\\ndb_path <- mk_united@dbpath\\nif (is.null(db_path)) db_path <- \\\"NA\\\"\\n\\n# Write the statistics to a TSV file\\nwrite.table(\\n  data.frame(n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path),\\n  file = \\\"output/unite_stats.tsv\\\",\\n  sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\",\\n  row.names = FALSE,\\n  col.names = TRUE\\n)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required